    Validate Ingested DublinCore Catalogs
    
    This patch makes the ingest service validate DublinCore catalogs when
    they are being ingested and returning a 400 Bad Request instead of
    accespting the request and failing afterwards with a broken workflow and
    a broken entry in the admin interface.
    
    To test this, just submit a broken DublinCore catalog like this:
    
    ```xml
     <dublincore xmlns="http://www.opencastproject.org/xsd/1.0/dublincore/"
         xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/"
         xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">
            <brokenxml
       <dcterms:creator>demo</dcterms:creator>
       <dcterms:contributor>demo</dcterms:contributor>
    ```
    
    This fixes #2127
